    "title" : "Intellectual Property"
  },
  "primaryContentSections" : [
    {
      "content" : [
        {
          "anchor" : "Definitions",
          "level" : 2,
          "text" : "Definitions",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "items" : [
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "code" : "Intellectual property",
                      "type" : "codeVoice"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : " - Creations of the mind that have value but can exist purely as data with no physical form.",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "code" : "Copyright",
                      "type" : "codeVoice"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : " - The legal right of owners to control the use and distribution of their intellectual property.",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "code" : "Licence",
                      "type" : "codeVoice"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : " - Official description of activities that are authorised or forbidden by the owner of intellectual property.",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            }
          ],
          "type" : "unorderedList"
        },
        {
          "anchor" : "Types-of-Software-Licences",
          "level" : 2,
          "text" : "Types of Software Licences",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "There are several types of software licences in order to avoid infringing copyright laws.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "tabs" : [
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "text" : "Software where the legal protections that are typically granted to intellectual property have either expired, surrendered or",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : " ",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : "are simply inapplicable. Not protected by copyright, anybody can legally copy, modify and distribute public domain software.",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "text" : "It may not always come with source code, though most do.",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ],
              "title" : "Public Domain Software"
            },
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "text" : "Software where users are given freedom to change, copy, study and share the software and its source code.",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "text" : "The term “free” refers to free to use, not free of charge.",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "text" : "Similar to public domain software, but is still protected under copyright and the copyright owners may use",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : " ",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : "this protection to require that the software must always be distributed with source code, attribution to the",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : " ",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : "original authors must be provided or any modifications must use a similar licence if distributed.",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "text" : "Other types of copyrighted works such as books, photographs and music can be licensed in a similar manner using",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : " ",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : "Creative Commons (CC) licences. Note that CC licences grant users freedom to copy, modify and distribute copyrighted",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : " ",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : "works, CC licences are not designed for software and should not be used for this purpose. It can, however, be",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : " ",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : "used to license content that is delivered using software. Highereducation course materials such sa videos and",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : " ",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : "notes created by universities and distributed for free on the Internet, aka open courseware often use CC licences.",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ],
              "title" : "Free and Open Source Software (FOSS)"
            },
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "text" : "Higher-education course materials such sa videos and notes created by universities and distributed for free on the Internet.",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ],
              "title" : "Open Courseware"
            },
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "text" : "Commercial software for which most of the legal protections under copyright are retained.",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "text" : "Unlike FOSS, it is usually not legal to copy, modify or distribute proprietary software. The terms and",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : " ",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : "conditions for which the proprietary software may or may not be used under copyright protection law are usually",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : " ",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : "communicated to users through an End User License Agreement (EULA) contract that the user must accept to use",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : " ",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : "the software.",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "text" : "The source code for proprietary software is usually kept secret.",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "text" : "Although it seems super restrictive compared to FOSS, it is important to remember that software is a form of",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : " ",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : "intellectual property and it is the right of the owner to be compensated for the use of the property.6. An example",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : " ",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : "of proprietary software is Windows OS, where unauthorised copying is illegal and the majority of source code is kept",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : " ",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : "secret.",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ],
              "title" : "Proprietary Software"
            },
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "text" : "Proprietary software that is available for use at no cost.",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "text" : "Some freeware are “lite” versions of proprietary software, allowing users to try a limited version of the software",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : " ",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : "while promoting the full version.",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ],
              "title" : "Freeware"
            },
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "text" : "Demonstration software that is distributed for free but for a specific evaluation period only.",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "text" : "After the evaluation period, the program expires and the user can no longer access the program unless the",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : " ",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : "user pays a registration fee.",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "text" : "The source code for freeware and shareware is usually kept secret and modifying the software is usually illegal.",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : " ",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : "However, it may be legal to copy and distribute freeware and shareware. Adobe Reader and Skype are examples of",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : " ",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : "freeware, and Camtasia Studio and WinRAR are examples of shareware.",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ],
              "title" : "Shareware"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "tabNavigator"
        },
        {
          "anchor" : "Software-Piracy",
          "level" : 2,
          "text" : "Software Piracy",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Software piracy is the crime of copying, distributing or using proprietary software illegally. Despite being illegal, it is",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "prevalent and can take place in many forms.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Installing multiple copies of proprietary software without purchasing additional licences or sharing proprietary software",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "with unlicensed users is considered software piracy and can result in similar legal repercussions.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Software piracy causes significant loss of revenue for the owners of intellectual property, which leads to higher prices for",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "legitimate buyers.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Cracks are programs that modify proprietary software so that the software cannot detect that it is being used illegally.",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "Software piracy is an example of copyright infringement, which is the use or distribution of copyrighted work without the",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "permission of the copyright owner. While software piracy is specific to software, copyright infringement can occur for any",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "copyrighted materials, such as pictures on the Internet, which is equivalent to theft.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Although all of this sounds extremely based and redpilled, we are legally required to condemn it.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "anchor" : "Plagiarism",
          "level" : 2,
          "text" : "Plagiarism",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Plagiarism is the cat of passing off someone else’s original work as your own, aka the act of claiming to be the author of a",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "piece of work without providing proper credit or attribution to the actual author.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Unlike copyright infringement, plagiarism may not always be illegal, but it is nevertheless an act of dishonestly and is usually",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "a punishable offence in academia.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Plagiarism can still occur when the original owner of a piece of work consents to letting someone else use it as their own.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "To avoid plagiarism, you can use ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "inlineContent" : [
                {
                  "text" : "citations",
                  "type" : "text"
                }
              ],
              "type" : "strong"
            },
            {
              "text" : " to give proper credit to the original authors of any reproduced materials in published",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "books, websites and articles.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "kind" : "content"
    }
